[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test results**\n\nThe build test result indicates that normal tests have passed, but I'm wondering if the instrumentation might exclude synthetic methods. The report seems to include this information. It could be that coverage is based on JaCoCo line coverage. I should take a closer look at class coverage with \"dynamic-access-coverage.json.\" It suggests that coverage isn't counted even if a method was executed, possibly due to JaCoCo not instrumenting dependency classes. There are several angles to explore here.\n\n**Investigating class issues**\n\nI'm wondering if the TagSupport class has a mismatch in the string \"javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.Tag\" compared to what javap shows, which is \"class$javax$servlet$jsp$tagext$Tag.\" There's a typo in the field name, but the string seems correct. It looks like Class.forName is only called if `Tag.class.isAssignableFrom(klass)`, which makes me think it needs to be dynamically loaded. If the test code imports Tag.class, that might explain why the library class field is null. I have a few angles to look into here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_081c2300878dfc8c0169f51ccb7710819098da572fd80ee8d0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9RzVgD5Ts9TGYCzAKc6HXnzHfFOFAGO4QMsQp3wGoMf-t7VW848FNROHZqslFuXtZMQPWRn4BXuBWDLy1tI4Gf8JAZN8ADOdqa54AWwanutRFW5p_NKhLIG63pMsEsmrvx6eKkdF3TXEA5QbvHxFsaZ1aBR0VTIaPrACY7rxOj5Be__E-b0h74zHWZcDVL29H5YpTgMPUZDPxWGsdXfyAIs9KMV-XDww8j2iwwxf42qVFaR-bX0mVy1SlU8Pdid2ZrlibL79U4AGoBqC7x_cOx9uXynf3aWbdLjElEQGtRFXo1Y9tkybtAdETfCVSSOOTorYwi0WV5wIfPFbD20AdCVlcsHXk8a2_yEunGze4qkZBL6J6KVpV2CprgQ3X50mQTvneVlU9_ctbOfGxYM9bSJ2yiMnyWhFUHpJ3R0Gl5PIZkSLvD3QZynSSxXFmX2B7qrO5J9mlsmsZPXlLbA0j_ekorjJUR09F0OHNM3ww43It2zaALcaCcqGpsUdBeU1P3LFIP2dMNTGzfWCpccWIfwOkqqxB1dtgvAp_50lY4lU9XcG7Oh3Ky1C-_Zdr9rR08LVvmGTIal7Ng_gs2gRVIYpD-l_eauhg1fLtjd7x0eoWswKGBGIH_JWAMZ0-HVdCTNloVvn9NxF0j8ehYtAHM